\h Beforeword
\mt1 Beforeword
\zbl|2\*
\ip Here is the Henoh's book in study format with footnotes and references.
\ip In the penultimate book, the book of Jude, the Bible mentions the book of Enoch, which was apparently known in Jesus' day. Later, for various reasons, but above all because it was so direct in its content towards sin, it was excluded from the books that would have been contained in the Bible.
\ip Reading the English version prompted us to translate it into Slovenian. In translating it, we added a few more references to the existing ones that link the book to the Bible, indicated by [square brackets].
\ip We pray that this book may be a blessing and encouragement to you in your walk with Jesus.
\ipr Translators
